                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271206-98-off495 t18271206-98-crimeloc498"></join>. On the 12th of November, about seven o'clock in the morning, the prisoner followed my boy into the shop, as he was taking down the shutters; I came from the parlour to the passage door - my wife, who was in the parlour, said, "He has got your coat;" I ran out, and caught him eight or ten yards off, with it doubled round him; it had hung on a chair in the shop, a few yards within the door.</p>
